task.summary: Default task
Adding support for popcount expressions. All expressions now return a CodeBlock rather than a String.
Fixing compile errors in generated code
Adding write method to BehaviorUnion. Write methods no longer include the simpleName.
Adding readMethod to BehaviorUnion

Adding JavaEvent which brings in the sumof expression. This changes the design of expressions that reference other fields. These expressions need to be able to reference the JavaType to create a CodeBlock using the correct ClassName. Expressions are now only evaluated in JavaUnits rather than XUnits.
Updating JavaEvent to get protocol after creation.
fixing ClientMessageDataUnion
Adding getNumber() to all events
Adding sentEvent to Events so we know if it was sent from a SendEvent request.
Adding sentEvent to Events so we know if it was sent from a SendEvent request.
Updating getSize in generated code to work with types and lists
Updating getSize for enums and enum lists
Adding padding to make sure events are 32 bytes
adding eventcopy support
Adding support for Errors
Making JavaUnit have a reference to javaType and xUnit. This allows more code to be shared between xunits.
Making JavaUnit have a reference to javaType and xUnit. This allows more code to be shared between xunits.
Adding checks for properties in XTypes. XTypes must have a result property.
Adding number to output of Events.
Adding write for error code in JavaError.
adding JavaRequest
Adding support for last list in JavaRequests
using getSizeExpression rather than fixedSize to increment javaStart in JavaRequest.

Converting objects to immutable values with a builder.

Moving all constants and extra fields to protocol in each x11 object.
